overview: "The user initiated a request for a thorough review of their sleep
  questionnaire application, aiming to validate its adherence to the Statement
  of Work and detailed specification. The agent conducted an in-depth analysis,
  identifying numerous gaps and missing features across various functionalities
  and sleep disorder detections. Following this review, a structured plan was
  generated, categorizing the missing items by priority. The agent then
  proceeded to implement the first high-priority item: integrating a 1-10
  tiredness severity scale into the questionnaire. This involved modifying data
  structures, updating validation logic, enhancing the user interface with a
  slider and conditional safety alerts, and ensuring these critical safety
  warnings were reflected in both the on-screen and PDF-generated narrative
  reports. This step significantly improved the questionnaire's ability to
  identify and flag severe tiredness, a key safety concern outlined in the
  original specification."
